description: Recently sold: $291,900. So much curb appeal and so many updates in this great home! The main level boasts updated kitchen with white cabinets, refinished countertops and brand new stainless appliances! Dining space leads to your very own private oasis - a private 17 x 35 paver patio! Upper level features vaulted owner bed, full bath w/ large Jacuzzi tub, second bedroom, spacious living room, and screen porch that boasts views of the wooded backyard! Lower level features large family room, big bedroom, an updated bath and tons of storage space! The beautiful backyard is fully fenced and offers another paver patio, a 10 x 10 veggie garden, and even the features of a swing set built right into the deck! Fresh paint throughout, new water heater in 2018, new AC in 2015, new sump pump in 2017, new windows in 2016, and so much more! See supplement for list! Close to Shamrock Park, McCullough Park, and Rice Creek North Regional Trail! Located in a great neighborhood in the coveted Mounds View school district!

description:
For sale: $339,900. Look no further than this newly remodeled 4 BR, 2 BA stunner! You wll be greeted with loads of natural sunlight as you step inside the foyer and on to the spacious LR w/an abundance of southerly-facing windows. Pratice your culinary skills in the open kitchen boasting granite countertops, subway tile backsplash, stainless appliances, pull out cabinet drawers, and breakfast bar. Move from the DR onto the large deck overlooking the .25 acre, fenced backyard or enjoy leisurely afternoons in the lower level FR. Each bedrooms has been lovingly appointed w/solid mission style doors and generous closet space while the huge master BR boasts a WIC w/laundry access. Both bathrooms have been impeccably updated w/the full bathroom sporting a granite vanity and glass mosaic tile. Additional upgrades include new flooring throughout, new fixtures and hardware, some newer 
Andersen windows, newer furnace and CA, maintenance free siding, newer roof, insulated garage w/workbench and convenient location!

Recently sold: $425,000. Incredibly updated with stunning curb appeal, this beautiful walk-up 4bd 3ba rambler has large updated windows to let the natural light in and enhance every space. Main level boasts wood floors, formal dining room, and 3 bedrooms, including master bath. Main floor living room is vaulted with stone fireplace and updated custom mantelpiece. Updated kitchen includes stainless appliances, peninsula/bar, and informal dining space. Kitchen and dining areas overlook the private spacious fenced yard with freshly painted deck and playset surrounded by majestic trees. Gorgeous updated main and LL baths. Ultimate entertainment area in LL with new projector, drop-down screen for movies and sports, gas burning fireplace, custom built-in cabinetry, and adjacent wet bar. Extras include a work shop in rear of garage and cement board exterior. Mounds View Schools.

description:
Recently sold: $273,000. This wonderful home is getting lots of updates! New kitchen with granite counters and stainless appliances! All 3 baths are getting updated. This home has large living spaces, large bedrooms and receives lots of natural light. Featuring 4 bedrooms, 3 full baths, a fireplace, deck, and an attached 2 car garage, you're sure to love living here! Currently being remodeled, this home will be available November 1. Great neighborhood and sought-after Mounds View School District (Island Lake Elementary, Chippewa Middle School, Mounds View High School). Conveniently located in Shoreview - easy access to 694, 35-W, 35-E. Just minutes to both Minneapolis and St. Paul downtown, Bethel, Northwestern College, Boston Scientific, Medtronic, Deluxe, Wells Fargo, walking distance to parks and lakes. Minutes drive from Blaine, Lino Lakes, Circle Pines, Lexington, Fridley, Columbia Heights, White Bear Lake, Arden Hills, New Brighton, Lauderdale, Roseville.

One-month's security deposit due at lease signing. Pets may be accepted with owner's approval and a pet deposit. There is a $30 non-refundable application fee per adult occupant. Tenants responsible for utilities.
All Applicants must:
-Have verifiable monthly income of at least 3 times rent
-Provide a government issued Photo ID
-Have reputable credit (minimum 600) and rental history
-No prior evictions, Judgements, UDs
-Agree to a full credit and background check.

Recently sold: $1,690,000. Welcome home to lakeshore living on the sandy shores of Turtle Lake! This walkout rambler sits on 2 1/2+ acres, has approximately 110' of lakeshore and is in the esteemed Mounds View School District. description:
Recently sold: $275,000. Welcome to this updated, well maintained, spacious split entry home.  	Immediately as you pull up you will be impressed with the maintenance free exterior and the recently painted front Deck.
	Step inside to the large Foyer.  There?s just enough space to greet guests and hang up coats!  
	Just past the Foyer is the handy Mudroom area.  This space is extremely convenient and offers a door to the Garage and access to the backyard and large Deck.
	Now go up the stairs to the large and open feeling Living Room/Dining Room.  
	The spacious Living Room has a custom paint job.The Dining Area has newer laminate flooring.  	The Kitchen is completely open to the Dining Area and has an island peninsula, tile floors and refaced Kitchen cabinets.  Don?t miss the stainless steel appliances.
	Just down the hall is the remodeled full Bathroom.  This larger than average Bathroom has subway tile, glass tile accents, and a large vessel sink and plenty of extra space for storage.  
	The two Bedrooms on this level are both spacious and have plenty of closet space.
	Just down the stairs is a fabulous Family Room, a 3/4 Bathroom and a generous sized third Bedroom.  Don?t miss the impressively clean Laundry and Work Room on this level              
          Inside..Outside..Truly a house you?ll want to call home!

Recently sold: $343,700. Don't miss out!  5+ bedrooms, 3 bath, beautifully kept!  Open main level with access to deck and yard, vaulted ceilings, quartz center island. Spacious master suite with private master bath.  Backs to private park reserve that is fun to explore.  Enjoy the quiet setting of this beautiful home!

HUGE fenced yard with inground sprinklers and freshly painted deck! HURRY!
Recently sold: $296,000.

description: Recently sold: $1,790,000. A true architectural marvel built by the prestigious Charles Cudd Builders, showcasing every space and detail designed with care. This luxury home is designed to nestle among the trees, with windows, decks, and patios offering panoramic views of Turtle Lake from almost every room or angle. The home is constructed out of lovely muted earth toned stone and brick, including the 5-car garage. The grounds, which are approx. 1 acre include landscaping complimentary to the home design, and a putting green in the back. The highlight of the grounds is the 100 ft. of sandy shoreline on Turtle Lake with plenty of room for a dock and a lakeside firepit. It is impossible to look at 985 Oakridge without appreciating the creativity and mastery of architecture. Much of the main floor is an open floor plan style, with incredible design accents ranging from stone columns, to a dramatically angled double floor-to-ceiling window, and a dramatic fireplace. As part of the open floor plan, the kitchen is perfect for entertaining and features all new appliances. Find privacy and elegance in the Master suite, which includes a bath with tub and shower, walk-in closet with thoughtfully designed built-in dressers, and a private balcony overlooking the lake. The lower level also offers ideal spaces for entertaining with a spacious media/family room, full wet bar, walk-out leading down to the lake, and a high-tech golf simulator! A perfect lakeshore location in Shoreview and over 5000 sf of impeccably designed beauty, don't miss out on the opportunity of 985 Oakridge!
